AIICO Insurance Plc has paid its policyholdrs N350 million claims within the first 48 hours of COVID-19 lockdown in the country in fulfilment of its commitment to prompt settlements. According to its executive director, Retail Business, Mr. Sola Ajayi, “We have been responding non-stop to our customers for payment of claims, policy loans, partial & full maturity benefits, among others, since the lockdown took effect. At AIICO, we are customer-centric; we put them first, and that differentiates us.” Similarly, the managing director/CEO, Mr Babatunde Fajemirokun, said, the company values the investment of trust by its customers in its ability to protect them against risks, even in tough times. “We have invested substantially in building capacity and developing capabilities for business continuity, irrespective of the challenging situations we will experience. Our robust Business Continuity Plan has enabled us to continue operations without hitches,” he pointed out. Stating that the company is also leveraging its technology platforms and digital channels for optimum service delivery, he added that the customer traffic on its digital platforms has increased tremendously in recent times and so far, it has been a delightful experience. The company has been actively running business operations by working remotely despite the COVID-19 disruption and has remained reachable to its customers. It advised stakeholders to keep safe during this period.